{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01XbSRrnoCPi9aC9QjLLHgAE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Etzi5Jr2nPWj4wWr9ct1JS","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n ray create configmap config-audit --from-literal=findings.txt=\"$(cat <<'AUDIT'\nRAY CLUSTER CONFIGURATION AUDIT\nNamespace: ray\nDate: 2026-06-23\nAuditor: automated read-only inspection (no cluster changes made)\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n1. WORKER REPLICA COUNT\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nCurrent: 3 (Deployment ray-worker, spec.replicas=3; 3/3 pods Ready)\nBaseline (kubectl.kubernetes.io/last-applied-configuration): 2\nDEVIATION: Worker replicas scaled up from 2 → 3.\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n2. IMAGE VERSIONS\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nray-head:   rayproject/ray:2.9.0\nray-worker: rayproject/ray:2.9.0\nBaseline:   rayproject/ray:2.9.0 (both components)\nDEVIATION:  None — images match baseline.\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n3. RESOURCE REQUESTS / LIMITS\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nray-head:   resources: {} (no requests or limits set)\nray-worker: resources: {} (no requests or limits set)\nBaseline:   resources: {} (both components)\nDEVIATION:  None vs baseline — however, absence of resource\n            constraints is a compliance gap (see recommendations).\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n4. SERVICE CONFIGURATION — ray-head (ClusterIP: 10.96.224.126)\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nCurrent ports:\n  - gcs:       6379/TCP → container 6379\n  - dashboard: 8265/TCP → container 8265\nBaseline (last-applied-configuration): single port only — gcs/6379.\nService type: ClusterIP (internal only, no external exposure).\nDEVIATION: Dashboard port 8265 added post-initial-deployment.\n\nRay head startup command (current):\n  ray start --head --include-dashboard=true --dashboard-host=0.0.0.0 \\\n            --port=6379 --num-cpus=0 --block\nBaseline startup command:\n  ray start --head --include-dashboard=false \\\n            --port=6379 --num-cpus=0 --block\nDEVIATION: Dashboard explicitly enabled (--include-dashboard=true,\n           --dashboard-host=0.0.0.0). This caused a pod rollout\n           (Deployment revision 1→2; old ReplicaSet ray-head-5c586c8fd6\n           still present at 0 replicas).\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n5. ACTIVE CONFIGMAPS\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nkube-root-ca.crt     — standard cluster CA certificate (Kubernetes-managed)\nrollback-rehearsal   — operator-authored rollback script documenting the\n                       two non-default changes (scale workers 3→2; remove\n                       dashboard port 8265). Contents confirm deviations\n                       found in this audit are intentional and tracked.\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n6. ADDITIONAL PODS OBSERVED (not part of standard deployments)\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\npod/curl-test    — Running (1/1); standalone pod, not managed by a Deployment\npod/ray-client   — Running (1/1); standalone pod, not managed by a Deployment\nThese are outside the standard cluster topology and should be reviewed\nto confirm they are authorized and ephemeral.\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n7. SUMMARY OF DEVIATIONS FROM BASELINE\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n  [DEVIATION-1] ray-worker replicas: 2 → 3 (scaled up)\n  [DEVIATION-2] ray-head dashboard: enabled (--include-dashboard=true,\n                --dashboard-host=0.0.0.0) — was disabled at baseline\n  [DEVIATION-3] ray-head Service: port 8265/dashboard added post-deploy\n  [NOTE]        Unmanaged pods (curl-test, ray-client) present in namespace\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n8. COMPLIANCE NOTES AND RECOMMENDATIONS\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nR1. [Resource limits] Both ray-head and ray-worker run without CPU/memory\n    requests or limits. This risks node resource starvation and OOM kills\n    under load. Set explicit requests/limits before the next change window.\n\nR2. [Dashboard exposure] The Ray dashboard (port 8265) is now reachable\n    within the cluster. The service type is ClusterIP (not externally\n    exposed), which limits blast radius, but any pod in the cluster can\n    reach the dashboard without authentication. Confirm this is intended;\n    if not, disable the dashboard or restrict access with a NetworkPolicy.\n\nR3. [Replica drift] The rollback-rehearsal ConfigMap confirms the worker\n    scale-up (2→3) is tracked and reversible. Ensure the change is\n    documented in the change management system and the rollback script\n    is tested before the next change window.\n\nR4. [Unmanaged pods] curl-test and ray-client are standalone pods with no\n    owning controller. They will not self-heal on node failure and their\n    purpose is not labeled. Review and remove if ephemeral, or wrap in a\n    Deployment/Job if persistent.\n\nR5. [Old ReplicaSet] ray-head-5c586c8fd6 (revision 1, 0 replicas) remains\n    in the namespace. This is normal Kubernetes rollout history but should\n    be cleaned up after the next change window if no rollback to revision 1\n    is anticipated.\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nEND OF AUDIT — no cluster changes were made during this inspection.\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\nAUDIT\n)\" 2>&1","description":"Create config-audit ConfigMap with audit findings"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens"